cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.RO 

The paper deals with learning 3D deformable object categories from raw single-view images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an autoencoder-based method for unsupervised learning, which involves learning from data without explicit supervision, making it likely to belong to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper deals with 3D objects, which involves geometry and topology, making it likely to belong to the sub-category cs.GR (Computer Graphics). The paper also involves reasoning about object symmetry, which involves logical reasoning, making it likely to belong to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves predicting symmetry probability maps, which involves probabilistic reasoning, making it likely to belong to the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics).
